* StrongArm Dynamic Comparator — DUT Subcircuit
* Technology: parameterized (L={L}, model via testbench .include)
*
* Ports (in order):
*   INP  — differential input (+)
*   INN  — differential input (−)
*   CLK  — clock
*   VDD  — positive supply
*   OUTP — digital output (+), HIGH when INP > INN
*   OUTN — digital output (−), HIGH when INN > INP
*
* Internal nodes (not ports):
*   VS   — tail source node
*   VXP  — integration node (+), discharges faster when INP is higher
*   VXN  — integration node (−)
*   VLP  — latch node (+)
*   VLN  — latch node (−)

.subckt comparator_strongarm INP INN CLK VDD OUTP OUTN

* ── Reset PMOS (M7–M10) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
* Gate = CLK.  ON when CLK=0 (reset phase): pull VXP/VXN/VLP/VLN to VDD.
* OFF when CLK=1 (evaluation phase).
M7  VXP CLK VDD VDD pmos W={W_rst}u L={L}
M8  VXN CLK VDD VDD pmos W={W_rst}u L={L}
M9  VLP CLK VDD VDD pmos W={W_rst}u L={L}
M10 VLN CLK VDD VDD pmos W={W_rst}u L={L}

* ── Tail NMOS (M0) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
* Gate = CLK.  ON when CLK=1: provides evaluation current path to GND.
M0 VS CLK 0 0 nmos W={W_tail}u L={L}

* ── Input differential pair (M1, M2) ─────────────────────────────────────────
* Drain = VXP/VXN (integration nodes).  Source = VS (tail).
* INP > INN → M1 draws more current → VXP discharges faster than VXN.
M1 VXP INP VS 0 nmos W={W_in}u L={L}
M2 VXN INN VS 0 nmos W={W_in}u L={L}

* ── NMOS latch (M3, M4) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
* Source = integration node (VXP / VXN).  Gate = cross-coupled latch node.
* Key: Vgs_M3 = VLN − VXP.  As VXP drops, Vgs_M3 rises → M3 turns ON
* and pulls VLP low through the chain GND→M0→M1→VXP→M3→VLP (NMOS regen phase).
M3 VLP VLN VXP 0 nmos W={W_lat_n}u L={L}
M4 VLN VLP VXN 0 nmos W={W_lat_n}u L={L}

* ── PMOS latch (M5, M6) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
* Cross-coupled.  When VLP drops far enough, M6 (gate=VLP) turns ON and pulls
* VLN toward VDD; simultaneously M5 (gate=VLN→VDD) turns OFF → full PMOS regen.
M5 VLP VLN VDD VDD pmos W={W_lat_p}u L={L}
M6 VLN VLP VDD VDD pmos W={W_lat_p}u L={L}

* ── Output inverters (M11–M14) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
* OUTP = NOT(VLP):  HIGH (=1) when VLP=0, i.e. when INP > INN.
* OUTN = NOT(VLN):  HIGH (=1) when VLN=0, i.e. when INN > INP.
* Both outputs are LOW (=0) during reset (VLP = VLN = VDD).
M11 OUTP VLP VDD VDD pmos W={W_inv_p}u L={L}
M12 OUTP VLP 0   0   nmos W={W_inv_n}u L={L}
M13 OUTN VLN VDD VDD pmos W={W_inv_p}u L={L}
M14 OUTN VLN 0   0   nmos W={W_inv_n}u L={L}

.ends comparator_strongarm
